The paper presents a model-based framework for robot locomotion using reinforcement learning, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of a loss function to track the model's prediction over multiple timesteps and the adaptation of model predictive control to account for planning latency suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of safe exploration during model learning suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of leg trajectories and the potential for various tasks suggest a possible application in computer vision (cs.CV).
